SELECT * FROM Vehicles;

SELECT Vehicles.make, COUNT(*) AS vehicle_count FROM Vehicles INNER JOIN Owners ON Vehicles.vehicle_id = Owners.owner_id GROUP BY Vehicles.make HAVING vehicle_count > 1;

SELECT Vehicles.make, Vehicles.model, Owners.full_name FROM Vehicles INNER JOIN Owners ON Vehicles.vehicle_id = Owners.owner_id WHERE Vehicles.year BETWEEN 2010 AND 2020 ORDER BY Vehicles.make ASC, Vehicles.model DESC;
SELECT * FROM AccessLogs INNER JOIN Permissions ON AccessLogs.owner_id = Permissions.owner_id WHERE Permissions.access_level = 'Admin' ORDER BY AccessLogs.access_time DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT Permissions.access_level, COUNT(*) AS access_count FROM Permissions GROUP BY Permissions.access_level ORDER BY access_count DESC;
